tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
Excellent service, quality and professionalism displayed by Dr Shaikh across multiple procedures and check ups.

I went to him Initially for a wisdom tooth removal, and then later for cavities.

I had cavaties which were almost going to be two root canals, other dentists were insisting on root canals even though i wasn't in pain, but Dr Aashiq explained the situation very well, spent lots of time in diagnosis and explanations and then saved me from a root canal, and instead very skillfully removed the cavity which was touching the tooth nerve. The process of filling and cosmetically re-shaping filling was done in such a way that no one can make out that anything was ever wrong with that area. 

Cavity removal and filling on two back teeth was painless and done within an hour in one single sitting.

Root canal was a difficult one, it took 3+ hours, and my case had a high risk of nerve damage, he explained the entire thing before hand along with where and how I would feel pain,  the procedure was mostly painless, with the unavoidable exception of  a few of the times that the nerve was pinched as the tooth was slowly taken out.
reply_text:
Thank you a lot for sharing your experience in such a fantastic way and appreciating the efforts that we take to save our patients teeth in every manner possible.
And moreover you have also been a fabulous patient and cooperative as well all through the procedure.
We find ourselves fortunate enough to have been got a chance to treat patients of your calibre.
Hope you have a healthy and happy life..ðŸ˜ƒ

tags: Treatment satisfaction,
review: Absolutely terrible experience. I wouldnâ€™t recommend anyone going to Dr. Aashiq at all after the experience Iâ€™ve had. I went to him because i had severe toothache due to an unfinished root canal done by my previous dentist. I was given 2 options of either extracting the tooth or attempting a re-root canal by the dr after looking at an x-ray that he took on the spot. I asked him what he recommended and he said that he would want me to give him a chance to save the tooth and so i did and we started the procedure immediately. I was prescribed anti inflammatorys and a painkiller ******* *** to be taken 3 times a day for 5 days. These 5 days were the most painful days of my life. After this when i went back to him i had a huge hard and painful swelling on my jaw which showed that i did have infection and that I should have been prescribed antibiotics for the same. ******* ** ******** *** ********** i was recommended to do an extraction and place an implant as soon as we extract the tooth to save time. Since I didnâ€™t want to lose my tooth i called up my family dr right after getting out of that clinic and told him the entire scenario* * *** **** **** **** ** ***** **** *** ********** **** ************* *** ****** *** **** ** ** **** ********* ****** *** ****** *********** *** * **** *** **** ** * ****** **** ** ************ It took me 3 days to recover from the pain but i still have a huge swelling filled with puss and infection. This was my experience with Dr. Aashiq and i feel the readers are smart enough to know what is best for them.
reply_text:
Thanks a lot for blaming us and negatively recommending us for wrong things done by your previous dentist.
Your previous doctor had broken an root canal cleaning instrument right at the apex of your tooth root while doing root canal procedure which definitely will cause you pain whether we prescribe antibiotics or not. 
We clarified this right at the time of consultation itself and gave you two options whether to extract or to give it a chance and save it. We mutually agreed to at least try and save it thinking it might work with your consent of course and explained you the possible pros and cons clearly.
What does informed consent mean?
Unfortunately your pain didnâ€™t subside as we had expected. So as discussed at the consultation appointment the other option was the only thing left to be implemented i.e extracting the tooth.
And this is what informed consent means.
But this option didnâ€™t go down your throat when the time arrived for it. You shouldnâ€™t have agreed upon for it at the first appointment itself and denied any sort of treatment at our clinic if you were not ready to get the tooth removed if the first option doesnâ€™t work.
You being a smart clever and well educated girl such a puerile behaviour was not expected at all especially after discussing each and every detail before hand.
As far as medications are concerned the doctor had cleared his stand on that day itself that until and and unless the source of infection (i.e the broken instrument) is either removed or bypassed completely or disinfected effectively the infection will recur again and again periodically ultimately transforming into a big abscess which might hurt you even more may be not today but surely some day later. This is what more than 13 years of experience of our expert doctor concludes.
Instead of thanking the doctor that he tried to save your tooth that too without even charging his fees for it, you are inappropriately recommending others not to go to him? He himself even personally messaged you the following day when the procedure was performed to know about your wellbeing. But you and your father didnâ€™t even show any respect for the doctor. That proves your immaturity and arrogance anyhow.
We are practising in this city since 13 years and encounter a lot of good calibre and high profile cases daily so performing treatments without prior consent is not at all our preference no matter whatever the situation would be. We never ever compromise on the standards and quality for that matter and we even charge for it extra if needed. 
We have tons of patients walking in and out but None of them have ever complained such a thing in past except you in these years.


Having said that we still hope the best for you in future and pray to Almighty for your complete recovery soon ðŸ˜Š 
May you stay blessed happy and healthy always..!!

review:
My experience with the doctor has really been amazing as he was the only dentist to give me my natural smile back.
I had multiple cavities in my teeth since i was young and multiple times these cavities were cleaned and filled up at different times by other dentists.
My neighbours suggested me to visit Dr. Aashiq Shaikh since they were also happy with the treatment provided by him.
Dr. Aashiq removed all my faulty fillings and crowns done earlier which were not fitting well with the gums and almost did 6 root canals for me and with minimal discomfort and suggested some cosmetic fillings and metal free ceramic crowns for me along with emax veneers for my front teeth.
Its been 6 months now and happy and satisfied with the treatment provided.
He took plenty of time and long appointments just to be perfect at every step *** *** *** ****** ** ** *** **** **********
Among all the earlier dentists i have visited before i would appreciate Dr. Aashiq's talent and his way of treating patients. Although he seems very young but i would give him 5star rating for his expertise..!!!

review:
It was an amazing experience with Dr. Aashiq as my dental phobia was totally eliminated forever which was with me since ages.
He is very very humble and polite and perfect in his work.

He had placed a rubber sheet which prevented water and the chemicals used for root canal treatment getting into my mouth and made my experience totally comfortable. Very dedicated and passionate doctor who really cares for his patients.

All together I recommend him strongly and wish him very good luck in future.
